    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-06-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-07-28T17:58:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an investment tax credit for five percent of the cost of a qualified truck. Defines &quot;qualified truck&quot; as a motor vehicle: (1) first placed in service on or after January 1, 2007, and before January 1, 2008; (2) powered by diesel fuel; (3) having a gross vehicle weight of more than 26,000 pounds; and (4) which complies with certain Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) regulations for diesel emissions. Allows such credit to reduce regular or alternative minimum tax liability. </p> <p>Permits a taxpayer election to expense the cost of qualified trucks placed in service in 2007.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
